POWERFUL AND FLEXIBLE FORMATTING WITH THE PIPETTE

​

The pipette is a fantastic tool for formatting. It memorizes all the characteristics of a shape, and you can apply them selectively later. A few ideas of what you can do:

  • Define a unique format for your titles instantaneously

  • Convert all bullets in your presentation to match a single style, taking each level of bullets into account,

  • Memorize a position and apply it on other slides

  • Apply the memorized size, color and position to a shape but without changing the style of its text

  • Adjust roundness of shapes

  • Equalize the dimensions of 2 charts

More

CREATING SLIDES HAS NEVER BEEN EASIER. POWER-USER BRINGS TOGETHER ON A SINGLE TAB ALL THE GREAT TOOLS YOU NEED TO WORK EFFICIENTLY
Same height/width

Equalize the height / width / size of your shapes. The 1st select shape is the reference.
Distribution

Increase / decrease horizontal spacing between shapes with a single click.
Swap position

Swap the position or text of 2 shapes.
Merge and split

Merge shapes, combining their respective text, or on the contrary split a shape into several shapes.
Select same shapes

Select all shapes matching criteria such as color, size, font, etc.
Organize

Organize shapes in a matrix with defined number of rows and columns.
Stack shapes

Stack shapes so that they are aligned with each shape just next to the other.
Symmetry

Position all selected shapes symmetrically versus a central axis.
Straigthen lines

Rectify lines and arrows so they are perfectly vertical or horizontal.

Text and shapes

Remove internal margins, fit text to shape or wrap text in shape, directly from the ribbon.

AUTOMATE TEDIOUS TASKS WITH OUR EXCEL ADD-IN UTILITIES

COPY-PASTE VISIBLE CELLS ONLY

​

A typical nightmare in Excel is when you want to copy filtered data from a column to another column. Excel will just ignore the filter and potentially ruin your data set! Wit Power-user you can simply copy and paste visible cells only to get yourself out of this painful situation.

More

UNPIVOT TABLE

​

This tool can save you hours. A situation that happens in Excel is when you have a crosstab table, but you want the data in the form of a database, where each row is duplicated for every column of your initial table. That's essential to create PivotTables for instance. Now that's something you can do instantly with Power-user's UnPivot Table!

More

MERGED CELLS MANAGER

​

Merged cells can be a nightmare for many Excel users, especially in databases or if you make VBA macros. Click the Merged Cells Manager and you will get a list of all merged cells in the active sheet. From there you will be able to view each merge cells, to unmerge them or to unmerge and fill them (a dream tool so you can create PivotTables).

More

DELETE EMPTY CELLS

​

Sometimes when working with data on Microsoft Excel, you need to move cells up eveytime there is a blank value. That is just what this utility will do for you, allowing you to remove empty cells from any selection.

More

ADVANCED FUNCTIONS

​

Get new powerful functions to use in your Excel formulas. These functions include SumColor, CountColor, CountUnique, CountVisible, IsMerged, HasFormulas, UsedRange, LastCell, Vlookup_Max, CAGR, and dozens more, but also Stock functions that will get market and financial data directly in your spreadsheet in near-real time.

More

CLEAN FORMULAS

​

When Excel formulas become complex, it does not help people understand or correct them if there are unnecessary redundancies. If you are working on Sheet1, you don't need to refer to 'Sheet1!A1' but just to 'A1'. Press Clean Formulas and Power-user will clean all formulas from such redundancies.

CHANGE FORMULAS ABSOLUTE / RELATIVE

​

If you realize after a while that you have used a relative 'A1' reference in many cells while you should have used an absolute 'A1'... it's not too late. This Power-user feature will let you make conversions in formulas between absolute, relative, relative column and absolute row or absolute column and relative row.
